               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Säʿatat za-lelit wa-za-nagh “Horologium for the Night and the Morning
                     Hours” (fols. 2r-63r): 
 I-1) Introductory prayers and hymns (fols. 2r-17r
                     l.10)
 I-2) Readings (fols. 17r l.10-21v l.12)
 I-3) Principal prayers
                     and hymns (fols. 21v l.13-63r)</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- About the text “Maṣḥafa Säʿatat” and the different versions, cp. EAE
                           V,<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ES501503">501-503</ref>. The text in Ms.<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESddm012">DDM-012</ref>seems to belong to the
                        category described as S.2.</note>
                     <note>- The text is similar, but not identical to Mss.<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESmr027">MR-027</ref>and<ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/ESqmm027">QMM-027</ref>.</note>
                     <note>- The Ms. contains most of the prayers and hymns included in the edition:
                        Maṣḥafa Säʿatat, ba-gǝʿǝzǝnna ba-ʾamarǝñña. Za-lelit wa-za-nagh, Addis Abäba
                        1952 A.M. [1960 A.D.].</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
